# Responsive Layouts

LexMastery supports:

Phones

Large Phones

Tablets

Foldables

Desktop (future)

---

# Philosophy

Design mobile-first.

Enhance progressively.

Never build desktop-first.

---

# Breakpoints

Compact

Medium

Expanded

Use adaptive layouts.

Never hardcode widths.

---

# Layout Rules

Compact

Single column

Medium

Adaptive spacing

Expanded

Multi-column where appropriate

---

# Cards

Cards should expand naturally.

Never use fixed widths.

---

# Lists

Support adaptive grid layouts.

Examples

2 columns

3 columns

4 columns

based on available width.

---

# Navigation

Phone

Bottom Navigation

Tablet

Navigation Rail

Desktop

Navigation Drawer

---

# Dialog Width

Dialogs should adapt to screen size.

Avoid full-width dialogs on tablets.

---

# Images

Images scale proportionally.

Never distort aspect ratio.

---

# Typography

Scale typography with screen size.

Maintain readability.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Generate adaptive layouts.

Avoid pixel-perfect assumptions.